  "prompt": "How can you locate the name of a proxy server?",
  "response": "There are several ways to locate the name of a proxy server:\n\n1. Browser settings:\n- Check browser network/connection settings\n- Look under proxy configuration options\n\n2. Operating system network settings:\n- Windows: Internet Options > Connections > LAN Settings\n- Mac: Network Preferences > Proxies\n\n3. Command line methods:\n- Windows: Use \"ipconfig\" or \"netsh\" commands\n- Mac/Linux: Use \"network\" or \"ifconfig\" commands\n\n4. Network configuration:\n- Check router settings\n- Review network administrator documentation\n\n5. System information tools:\n- Use network diagnostic tools\n- Check system network configuration panels\n\n6. Online proxy detection websites:\n- Use websites that can detect and display proxy information\n\n7. Application-specific proxy settings:\n- Check individual application network configurations\n\n8. System registry (Windows):\n- Examine registry keys related to network configuration\n\n9. Network diagnostic software:\n- Use specialized network analysis tools\n\n10. Ask network administrator:\n- Directly inquire about proxy server details\n\nThe specific method depends on your system, network configuration, and access level.",
